Pyo In Sook couldn't explain how she killed Park Du Jin,

77
00:05:21,020 --> 00:05:24,690
and there are a lot of suspicious aspects of the third murder's crime scene.

78
00:05:24,690 --> 00:05:26,600
Bring the evidence!

79
00:05:26,600 --> 00:05:31,350
Don't keep talking about there being no evidence, and bring some evidence!

80
00:05:31,350 --> 00:05:33,760
A witness has appeared.

81
00:05:33,760 --> 00:05:35,930
- Where? 
 - Gosan Station.

82
00:05:40,360 --> 00:05:42,000
Are you okay?

83
00:05:45,370 --> 00:05:47,170
Wait a moment.

84
00:05:55,460 --> 00:05:58,210
- It's all over. 
 - We just need to go a little further.

85
00:05:58,210 --> 00:06:00,940
- Why that picture? 
 - What?

86
00:06:00,940 --> 00:06:03,160
That's my least favorite picture.

87
00:06:03,160 --> 00:06:07,770
When that picture was taken, I said that I didn't want to,

88
00:06:07,770 --> 00:06:11,180
but my grandma dressed me in that red outfit.

89
00:06:11,180 --> 00:06:13,570
But the background was red.

90
00:06:13,570 --> 00:06:16,780
So everything but my face was red.

91
00:06:16,780 --> 00:06:19,680
Like my neck was floating alone.

92
00:06:19,680 --> 00:06:24,640
But since that picture is coming out and being labeled a serial killer,

93
00:06:24,640 --> 00:06:27,240
it fits too well.

94
00:06:27,240 --> 00:06:29,730
No, it's pretty.

95
00:06:29,730 --> 00:06:33,900
And why you? Why are you wanted, too?

96
00:06:33,900 --> 00:06:37,730
It's not you. If you get tangled up too...

97
00:06:37,730 --> 00:06:39,890
I'm okay.

98
00:06:39,890 --> 00:06:43,080
- If we get caught like this... 
 - We won't get caught.

99
00:06:43,080 --> 00:06:46,690
Listen up. We only need to go a little further.

100
00:06:46,690 --> 00:06:49,190
A long as we get out of here, there won't be any CCTV.

101
00:06:49,190 --> 00:06:51,330
We only need to run a little more.

102
00:06:52,340 --> 00:06:54,280
Will you be able to run?

103
00:07:02,070 --> 00:07:03,730
Let's go.

104
00:07:10,020 --> 00:07:12,780

105
00:07:14,040 --> 00:07:15,530
This is really unbelievable.

106
00:07:15,530 --> 00:07:20,160
What the hell is this? They killed someone else?

107
00:07:20,160 --> 00:07:24,220
Woo Cheon was the one who put the moss rose in the first place.

108
00:07:24,220 --> 00:07:28,530
But another corpse with that flower showed up again...

109
00:07:28,530 --> 00:07:31,980
Another one? Did Woo Cheon actually–

110
00:07:31,980 --> 00:07:34,180
We started this.

111
00:07:34,950 --> 00:07:40,450
But... after that, I really don't know what happened.

112
00:07:41,520 --> 00:07:44,230
A serial killer and a hitman?

113
00:07:44,230 --> 00:07:47,730
Isn't this too dramatic?

114
00:07:47,730 --> 00:07:52,490
But I think In Sook is hurt.

115
00:07:52,490 --> 00:07:55,160
I think she collapsed.

116
00:07:56,380 --> 00:07:59,690
What the hell? These guys are doing a face assessment at a time like this?

117
00:07:59,690 --> 00:08:01,710
These crazy assholes.

118
00:08:01,710 --> 00:08:05,290
You jerks, talk after having a look at yourself!

119
00:08:23,230 --> 00:08:25,670
Let's go to Venice.

120
00:08:25,670 --> 00:08:28,950
Huh? How can we go abroad in a situation like this?

121
00:08:28,950 --> 00:08:32,210
Tae Il Hyung will prepare forged passports and tickets.

122
00:08:32,210 --> 00:08:34,630
Just hang in there for a little longer.

123
00:08:37,110 --> 00:08:39,030
It's okay.

124
00:08:41,670 --> 00:08:44,700
There are times when things are really urgent.

125
00:08:44,700 --> 00:08:49,410
When I'm late for an appointment... or just when things are urgent,

126
00:08:49,410 --> 00:08:52,670
I run like the wind and get on the bus,

127
00:08:52,670 --> 00:08:57,680
and look out the window. To get rid of my nerves.

128
00:08:59,480 --> 00:09:02,420
Because for these 30 minutes when I'm on the bus,

129
00:09:02,420 --> 00:09:05,660
nothing changes, no matter what I do.

130
00:09:05,660 --> 00:09:09,690
So I think, "Let's just rest. Let go."

131
00:09:10,750 --> 00:09:14,620
"Being nervous will change nothing."

132
00:09:17,670 --> 00:09:20,330
We'll be all right for an hour.

133
00:09:20,330 --> 00:09:24,130
After that, the sun will set. Let's move then.

134
00:09:28,500 --> 00:09:32,980
But is this cathedral... really safe?

135
00:09:32,980 --> 00:09:36,270
Yeah. It's too far out, so we'll be okay.

136
00:09:36,270 --> 00:09:38,910
How did you know about this place?

137
00:09:39,790 --> 00:09:42,140
I came from time to time.

138
00:09:42,140 --> 00:09:44,030
Why?

139
00:09:44,030 --> 00:09:45,830
To pray.

140
00:09:45,830 --> 00:09:49,720
- What kind of prayer? 
 - I don't remember.

141
00:09:49,720 --> 00:09:51,690
I think I was begging for something.

142
00:09:51,690 --> 00:09:54,240
Let's try once.

143
00:09:54,240 --> 00:09:56,900
Do you have anything to pray for?

144
00:09:56,900 --> 00:09:59,110
No.

145
00:09:59,110 --> 00:10:01,260
You don't?

146
00:10:01,260 --> 00:10:02,870
Yeah.

147
00:10:05,930 --> 00:10:11,360
Because I'm fine right now since you're by my side.

148
00:10:12,750 --> 00:10:15,080
Everything is all right.

149
00:10:33,600 --> 00:10:35,550
San Ah!

150
00:10:38,720 --> 00:10:41,020
Are you okay now?

151
00:10:41,020 --> 00:10:44,050
That's a relief. Then, should we go play outside?

152
00:10:44,050 --> 00:10:45,190
Sure.

153
00:10:45,190 --> 00:10:47,140
We'll be playing in the yard.

154
00:10:47,140 --> 00:10:49,340
All right, go on.

155
00:10:53,020 --> 00:10:55,980
You came to cook in the middle of all this?

156
00:10:55,980 --> 00:10:58,330
Are you going to be okay?

157
00:10:58,330 --> 00:11:01,310
I feel like I'm being possessed by a ghost.

158
00:11:02,650 --> 00:11:05,280
Don't you tell fortunes? Can you have a look at mine?

159
00:11:05,280 --> 00:11:07,320
How did this happen?

160
00:11:07,320 --> 00:11:09,210
I'm not a person that sees those kinds of things.

161
00:11:09,210 --> 00:11:10,600
Then, what do you see?

162
00:11:10,600 --> 00:11:12,860
You may say that I see people's energy.

163
00:11:12,860 --> 00:11:18,840
Everyone has a color, I look at that and read their luck.

164
00:11:18,840 --> 00:11:21,700
She's a con artist.

165
00:11:21,700 --> 00:11:24,710
You know that your color is quite dark, right?

166
00:11:24,710 --> 00:11:27,400
Nothing is clear, it's just dark all the way through.

167
00:11:27,400 --> 00:11:30,880
So, will I live if I'm dark all the way through?

168
00:11:30,880 --> 00:11:32,390
What color do you turn when you die?

169
00:11:32,390 --> 00:11:36,080
That's not it! You die when you turn all white.

170
00:11:36,080 --> 00:11:38,450
So annoying!

171
00:11:38,450 --> 00:11:40,240
Does this make any sense?

172
00:11:40,240 --> 00:11:43,310
In Sook just said that she wanted to look at Woo Cheon's face one time,

173
00:11:43,310 --> 00:11:46,130
she ran away to see him even one time.

174
00:11:46,130 --> 00:11:49,520
Since the police can't catch the real culprit,

175
00:11:49,520 --> 00:11:51,450
they're placing the blame on them.

176
00:11:51,450 --> 00:11:53,530
Right? That's what's happening, right?

177
00:11:53,530 --> 00:11:57,990
Even still, it is quite refreshing. That man who beat his girlfriend to death died for the best.

178
00:11:57,990 --> 00:11:59,840
People don't even pray for the souls of guys like that.

179
00:11:59,840 --> 00:12:02,000
Maybe it's because I have a daughter too,

180
00:12:02,000 --> 00:12:06,590
but I started shaking when I saw that article. How could someone beat someone up like that?

181
00:12:06,590 --> 00:12:08,780
Is that even human?

182
00:12:08,780 --> 00:12:10,490
Hitman?

183
00:12:10,490 --> 00:12:14,470
What's the deal with them saying that Woo Cheon did something like that?

184
00:12:14,470 --> 00:12:19,000
Did In Sook really end up like this because she got involved with him?

185
00:12:21,300 --> 00:12:23,280
Did you see In Sook?

186
00:12:23,280 --> 00:12:26,400
- Before she left here? 
 - Yeah.

187
00:12:26,400 --> 00:12:28,520
She was really sick.

188
00:12:28,520 --> 00:12:30,820
Did they say she was dying?

189
00:12:32,300 --> 00:12:36,080
All of the people here are dying.

190
00:12:36,080 --> 00:12:38,720
Why do you say something like that like it's nothing?

191
00:12:38,720 --> 00:12:41,690
Obviously, it's not nothing...

192
00:12:42,480 --> 00:12:45,090
My mom died, too.

193
00:12:46,610 --> 00:12:49,290
Are you okay?

194
00:12:49,290 --> 00:12:52,170
You miss your mom, don't you?

195
00:12:52,170 --> 00:12:57,250
Sometimes I forget... that my mom is not here.

196
00:12:57,250 --> 00:13:00,820
It's better when I forget, so I keep trying to.

197
00:13:00,820 --> 00:13:03,760
"My mom is really gone."

198
00:13:03,760 --> 00:13:07,970
When I feel like that, I get really scared.

199
00:13:07,970 --> 00:13:13,310
Everything would be all right if I just had my mom, but she's the only thing that's missing.

200
00:13:13,310 --> 00:13:19,880
What if I live here with you, too?

201
00:13:19,880 --> 00:13:24,160
Why? What about your mom?

202
00:13:24,160 --> 00:13:27,570
No... I was just thinking.

203
00:13:27,570 --> 00:13:29,600
A thought.

204
00:13:57,550 --> 00:13:59,840
What did you do?

205
00:14:00,690 --> 00:14:02,720
I prayed.

206
00:14:02,720 --> 00:14:05,620
What did you say?

207
00:14:05,620 --> 00:14:08,080
I asked for forgiveness.

208
00:14:08,080 --> 00:14:09,650
For what?

209
00:14:09,650 --> 00:14:15,970
I begged to be forgiven for my sins.

210
00:14:26,600 --> 00:14:31,840
When did things start going wrong?

211
00:14:36,970 --> 00:14:39,670
When I was in middle school.

212
00:14:41,650 --> 00:14:44,850
I killed a classmate of mine.

213
00:14:47,220 --> 00:14:52,820
We got in a fight, and it was an accident.

214
00:14:52,820 --> 00:15:00,100
But now that I think about it, I think that I thought

215
00:15:00,100 --> 00:15:03,770
that I would like it if he died.

216
00:15:03,770 --> 00:15:07,100
That kid gave me a really hard time.

217
00:15:07,100 --> 00:15:10,650
So could it have been an accident?

218
00:15:10,650 --> 00:15:18,830
Or... did he die because I had those kinds of feelings?

219
00:15:18,830 --> 00:15:21,020
It was an accident.

220
00:15:21,020 --> 00:15:24,460
His family was really rich.

221
00:15:25,900 --> 00:15:28,940
His mom had only one son.

222
00:15:28,940 --> 00:15:36,240
That mom followed me my whole life and made me suffer.

223
00:15:37,150 --> 00:15:42,410
So that I couldn't do anything, so that I couldn't even breathe.

224
00:15:43,780 --> 00:15:50,090
So even when my mom died, we couldn't even go to the hospital.

225
00:15:51,590 --> 00:15:54,520
No one helped us.

226
00:15:55,440 --> 00:16:01,210
Did that fix it? Did that make things even?

227
00:16:01,210 --> 00:16:04,220
Should I just die, too?

228
00:16:06,190 --> 00:16:09,400
I lived while only thinking things like that.

229
00:16:17,420 --> 00:16:20,380
But since I met you,

230
00:16:23,090 --> 00:16:26,270
I started wanting to be forgiven.

231
00:16:56,140 --> 00:16:58,640
I'm becoming quite devout.

232
00:16:58,640 --> 00:17:02,730
But... this is the only method we have, isn't it?

233
00:17:02,730 --> 00:17:05,390
No one will recognize us.

234
00:17:06,300 --> 00:17:09,350
I think I'm beginning to feel at peace.

235
00:17:16,150 --> 00:17:18,790
It's like we're going on a trip.

236
00:17:19,540 --> 00:17:21,760
We are going on a trip.

237
00:17:29,650 --> 00:17:36,270
These days, I keep thinking of that woman's face.

238
00:17:36,270 --> 00:17:40,430
At one point, I hated and resented her,

239
00:17:40,430 --> 00:17:43,200
and wondered if I should get revenge.

240
00:17:43,200 --> 00:17:46,990
I wanted to question her about whether she was finally satisfied...

241
00:17:48,510 --> 00:17:53,220
But the last time I saw her face, how should I say...

242
00:18:02,180 --> 00:18:04,190
 What can I do?

243
00:18:04,190 --> 00:18:08,640
 Aside from the part that hates you, my entire heart is sad.

244
00:18:08,640 --> 00:18:11,470
 My heart feels like it will break open,

245
00:18:11,470 --> 00:18:14,260
 so I should fill it with loathing.

246
00:18:16,030 --> 00:18:18,960
I think that I might understand.

247
00:18:23,280 --> 00:18:30,990
If you were to die like this, I might even kill Koo Ji Pyo.

248
00:18:30,990 --> 00:18:36,180
While following him for my whole life, I might even kill him.

249
00:18:38,580 --> 00:18:41,570
So don't give up like this.

250
00:18:47,690 --> 00:18:50,820

251
00:18:50,820 --> 00:18:55,010
The room on the second floor is clean and has an amazing view.

252
00:18:55,010 --> 00:18:59,270
But is it all right for a nun and a priest to share a room?

253
00:18:59,270 --> 00:19:02,510
Yes, yes. We are all right.

254
00:19:02,510 --> 00:19:06,780
In the business spreading the word, there's no night and day, nor man and woman.

255
00:19:06,780 --> 00:19:09,010
Amen.

