00:43:30,390 --> 00:43:32,900
That's what I'm most afraid of these days.

524
00:43:32,900 --> 00:43:35,270
Don't say things like that.

525
00:43:36,030 --> 00:43:39,000
Once you leave after getting married,

526
00:43:39,660 --> 00:43:42,300
I'll be left alone.

527
00:43:45,490 --> 00:43:48,140
That's a relief.

528
00:43:48,140 --> 00:43:52,630
Spending time with you and In Sook,

529
00:43:52,630 --> 00:43:54,790
together,

530
00:43:55,450 --> 00:43:57,700
made me happy.

531
00:43:59,820 --> 00:44:01,620
What's wrong with you?

532
00:44:01,620 --> 00:44:04,320
Stop saying things like that.

533
00:44:14,670 --> 00:44:17,060
Hello.

534
00:44:17,060 --> 00:44:19,130
Wait a minute.

535
00:44:21,660 --> 00:44:24,430
Unnie is not okay right now.

536
00:44:24,430 --> 00:44:27,110
Oh, really?

537
00:44:27,110 --> 00:44:30,830
I saw the article. Congrats.

538
00:44:32,260 --> 00:44:34,000
Thank you.

539
00:44:36,400 --> 00:44:38,820
Mi Do, want to go look for a house?

540
00:44:38,820 --> 00:44:42,330
A house? Who's house?

541
00:44:42,330 --> 00:44:45,930
- Our house. 
 - Our house?!

542
00:44:45,930 --> 00:44:49,400
I'm checking CCTV footage of pharmacies and hospitals in the area,

543
00:44:49,400 --> 00:44:51,670
but nothing is coming up.

544
00:44:52,230 --> 00:44:54,610
We don't have the time to check all that.

545
00:45:00,270 --> 00:45:02,640
Cha Myeong Ju.

546
00:45:02,640 --> 00:45:04,770
Cha Myeong Ju.

547
00:45:06,360 --> 00:45:08,520
Cha Myeong Ju.

548
00:45:30,330 --> 00:45:34,560
Where are we?

549
00:45:34,560 --> 00:45:38,530
- Are you okay? 
 - Yeah.

550
00:45:43,950 --> 00:45:46,050
Who is this?

551
00:45:47,270 --> 00:45:49,660
That kid.

552
00:45:49,660 --> 00:45:53,880
The friend... I killed.

553
00:45:57,820 --> 00:46:00,750
That kid's mother helped us.

554
00:46:02,050 --> 00:46:04,800
You were forgiven.

555
00:46:15,070 --> 00:46:17,620
What a relief.

556
00:46:19,100 --> 00:46:21,620
Really a relief.

557
00:46:48,870 --> 00:46:51,940
Go buy anything you want at the department store.

558
00:46:51,940 --> 00:46:54,630
I'll set a date for the wedding as soon as possible.

559
00:46:54,630 --> 00:46:56,460
Really?

560
00:46:57,630 --> 00:47:00,560
Am I really going to live in this house?

561
00:47:00,560 --> 00:47:04,260
Of course. That's the bedroom.

562
00:47:04,260 --> 00:47:06,570
I ordered the bed first.

563
00:47:06,570 --> 00:47:09,060
I can't believe it.

564
00:47:11,690 --> 00:47:16,260
Ever since I was young, I liked dramatic things.

565
00:47:16,260 --> 00:47:19,390
But life... isn't really like that.

566
00:47:19,390 --> 00:47:22,230
It's pitiful and boring.

567
00:47:22,230 --> 00:47:26,760
Ever since I've become terminally ill,

568
00:47:26,760 --> 00:47:30,610
everything's become so theatrical.

569
00:47:30,610 --> 00:47:33,060
Maybe that's why I'm here.

570
00:47:33,060 --> 00:47:35,850
But I'm not sure...

571
00:47:35,850 --> 00:47:39,490
if it's okay for me to be so happy

572
00:47:39,490 --> 00:47:41,610
all alone.

573
00:47:41,610 --> 00:47:43,530
You can.

574
00:47:44,410 --> 00:47:46,840
- Really? 
 - Yes.

575
00:47:48,910 --> 00:47:54,860
I heard somewhere that when you meet someone you really want to be with,

576
00:47:54,860 --> 00:47:59,830
when you live a sincere life, you don't need to be reborn.

577
00:48:00,430 --> 00:48:03,540
I guess I won't need to be reborn, either.

578
00:48:03,540 --> 00:48:05,440
Right?

579
00:48:32,950 --> 00:48:35,980
It's been a while since I've prepared breakfast.

580
00:48:38,960 --> 00:48:41,410
I set aside some medicine as well.

581
00:48:53,450 --> 00:48:56,700
You're not at the bottom, it's a relief.

582
00:48:56,700 --> 00:48:59,670
You're not miserable, it's a relief.

583
00:48:59,670 --> 00:49:02,990
I was breaking down, just like you.

584
00:49:06,670 --> 00:49:09,090
Protect her well.

585
00:49:24,990 --> 00:49:26,890
What's this? What's going on?

586
00:49:26,890 --> 00:49:30,070
She suddenly started convulsing, and her anemia has gotten worse.

587
00:49:30,070 --> 00:49:32,610
Unnie. Unnie, are you okay?

588
00:49:32,610 --> 00:49:34,320
What's wrong with you suddenly?

589
00:49:34,320 --> 00:49:36,400
The house.

590
00:49:36,400 --> 00:49:39,340
- What? 
 - Did you get to see your house?

591
00:49:39,340 --> 00:49:42,500
That's not important right now.

592
00:49:42,500 --> 00:49:46,000
Unnie, you'll be okay.

593
00:49:46,000 --> 00:49:48,500
If you die like this, I'll kill you.

594
00:49:48,500 --> 00:49:51,320
She's not going to die.

595
00:49:51,930 --> 00:49:53,910
Unnie.

596
00:50:20,320 --> 00:50:22,140
 One, two, three.

597
00:50:22,140 --> 00:50:24,240
 One, two, three.

598
00:50:34,190 --> 00:50:37,790
 We're in this together. On the same side!

599
00:51:26,870 --> 00:51:30,590
Why didn't you tell me your condition had gotten so poor?

600
00:51:30,590 --> 00:51:34,290
The doctors said your symptoms must've been severe.

601
00:51:34,290 --> 00:51:36,530
Just because.

602
00:51:36,530 --> 00:51:40,290
I had too many things to do.

603
00:51:45,130 --> 00:51:47,890
While staying at the hospice,

604
00:51:47,890 --> 00:51:52,530
I noticed all cancer patients die suddenly.

605
00:51:52,530 --> 00:51:54,440
They're fine one day,

606
00:51:54,440 --> 00:51:58,540
but their conditions worsen suddenly, over a week.

607
00:51:59,160 --> 00:52:01,360
Out of nowhere.

608
00:52:01,360 --> 00:52:06,220
I don't know when it started, but every morning,

609
00:52:07,130 --> 00:52:10,020
I started getting scared

610
00:52:11,070 --> 00:52:13,240
that day would come to me, too.

611
00:52:28,000 --> 00:52:30,000
You've grown into a charismatic woman.

612
00:52:30,000 --> 00:52:32,360
Have a seat here.

613
00:52:38,940 --> 00:52:42,210
Parents don't know their children.

614
00:52:42,210 --> 00:52:46,680
It's a mistake to think they know everything, just because they gave birth to them.

615
00:52:48,350 --> 00:52:52,000
I had always crossed the line.

616
00:52:52,000 --> 00:52:57,040
It wasn't for you, but for me.

617
00:52:58,110 --> 00:53:00,730
I wanted you to be

618
00:53:00,730 --> 00:53:04,100
in the place I wanted you to be.

619
00:53:04,100 --> 00:53:07,160
That's why I wouldn't let you be.

620
00:53:07,160 --> 00:53:09,740
- I... 
 - Mom.

621
00:53:09,740 --> 00:53:12,660
I always leaned on you.

622
00:53:12,660 --> 00:53:15,990
You were my child,

623
00:53:15,990 --> 00:53:22,270
my husband, my friend, my everything.

624
00:53:22,270 --> 00:53:27,550
So I placed too much of a burden on you.

625
00:53:27,550 --> 00:53:29,610
I'm sorry.

626
00:53:31,080 --> 00:53:34,440
You don't have to worry about me anymore.

627
00:53:34,440 --> 00:53:37,090
I'm living with a widowed friend and it's nice.

628
00:53:37,090 --> 00:53:39,430
It's so fun.

629
00:53:40,840 --> 00:53:42,870
What a relief.

630
00:53:45,800 --> 00:53:48,980
I'm going to stand on my own now.

631
00:53:48,980 --> 00:53:52,290
I'm going to live my life to its fullest.

632
00:53:52,290 --> 00:53:54,740
So don't worry about me,

633
00:53:54,740 --> 00:53:57,940
and stand up yourself.

634
00:53:57,940 --> 00:54:01,570
Don't worry too much. She'll get up.

635
00:54:01,570 --> 00:54:05,740
Yoon Seo, thank you.

636
00:54:13,310 --> 00:54:17,160
We caught them on CCTV footage near Cha Myeong Ju's Pediatric Clinic.

637
00:54:17,160 --> 00:54:19,520
Salutations.

638
00:54:19,520 --> 00:54:21,940
Where are they?

639
00:54:21,940 --> 00:54:24,820
We've confirmed through CCTV footage that they escaped with the clinic director.

640
00:54:24,820 --> 00:54:28,240
- Why would they escape with the clinic director? 
 - Min Woo Cheon is acquainted with her.

641
00:54:28,240 --> 00:54:30,490
- In middle school, Min Woo Ch— 
 - Request support ASAP.

642
00:54:30,490 --> 00:54:32,490
- Go surround her house. 
 - Understood.

643
00:54:32,490 --> 00:54:35,180
Let's go! Come on!

644
00:54:50,720 --> 00:54:54,290

645
00:55:09,140 --> 00:55:11,260
Is it you, In Sook?

646
00:55:12,660 --> 00:55:14,420
What're you here for?

647
00:55:14,420 --> 00:55:17,580
There are police everywhere!

648
00:55:17,580 --> 00:55:20,170
I have nowhere to go.

649
00:55:22,500 --> 00:55:25,620
I'm sure In Sook doesn't have anywhere to go either.

650
00:55:30,210 --> 00:55:32,600
Goodness!

651
00:55:32,600 --> 00:55:35,540
I'm crazy! My daughter is dying

652
00:55:35,540 --> 00:55:38,970
and I blabbered on and on about Venice being Heaven.

653
00:55:38,970 --> 00:55:41,700
Crazy!

654
00:55:50,790 --> 00:55:53,800
- They said they were going to Venice. 
 - What?

655
00:55:53,800 --> 00:55:57,480
She said she was going to Venice with Woo Cheon.

656
00:55:57,480 --> 00:55:59,710
Do you think they made it?

657
00:55:59,710 --> 00:56:02,150
Venice?

658
00:56:02,150 --> 00:56:06,400
You know that kid, Woo Cheon.

659
00:56:06,400 --> 00:56:08,300
Is he really a hit man?

660
00:56:08,300 --> 00:56:11,070
I don't know! I don't understand

661
00:56:11,070 --> 00:56:12,820
anything that's going on.

662
00:56:12,820 --> 00:56:15,080
He didn't seem like one.

663
00:56:15,080 --> 00:56:17,270
You met him?

664
00:56:17,270 --> 00:56:20,200
They came to my shop once.

665
00:56:20,200 --> 00:56:23,460
- Really? 
 - She said he was her boyfriend.

666
00:56:24,290 --> 00:56:26,790
It felt strange.

667
00:56:26,790 --> 00:56:29,860
But I didn't dislike him.

668
00:56:29,860 --> 00:56:33,880
He seemed like he had a screw loose in his head,

669
00:56:33,880 --> 00:56:36,670
but he reminded me a bit of myself.

670
00:56:36,670 --> 00:56:38,950
They say daughters tend to meet men like their fathers—

671
00:56:38,950 --> 00:56:41,700
Absolutely not! That won't do.

672
00:56:41,700 --> 00:56:44,940
Right, that won't do.

673
00:56:47,220 --> 00:56:52,040
I wonder wherever they are if they've been eating properly.

674
00:56:52,040 --> 00:56:54,060
What are they doing?

675
00:56:54,060 --> 00:56:56,480
My heart aches so much I could die.

676
00:56:56,480 --> 00:56:59,180
Mom, I don't think this is right.

677
00:56:59,180 --> 00:57:01,140
They didn't do it!

678
00:57:01,140 --> 00:57:03,560
Must we just sit back and watch?

679
00:57:03,560 --> 00:57:06,020
Shouldn't we be protesting somewhere?

680
00:57:06,020 --> 00:57:09,050
Shouldn't we step up?

681
00:57:11,780 --> 00:57:13,990
It's fun.

682
00:57:17,080 --> 00:57:18,240
Huh?

683
00:57:18,240 --> 00:57:20,770
I briefly saw the news earlier,

684
00:57:20,770 --> 00:57:24,110
and we're heroes.

685
00:57:24,110 --> 00:57:28,480
Janitors that clean the trash of this world.

686
00:57:28,480 --> 00:57:33,790
Sure, I started all of this.

687
00:57:33,790 --> 00:57:37,150
I told myself I would take a bad guy with me.

688
00:57:38,710 --> 00:57:41,570
I'm sure that was anger.

689
00:57:41,570 --> 00:57:44,970
Anger towards the world that couldn't protect a single child,

690
00:57:44,970 --> 00:57:48,550
and towards the world that ostracized me.

691
00:57:48,550 --> 00:57:54,140
But things have spiraled out of my control

692
00:57:54,840 --> 00:57:57,930
and we're running for our lives.

693
00:58:03,860 --> 00:58:06,570
When will this end?

694
00:58:08,840 --> 00:58:11,540
How will it end?

695
00:58:25,150 --> 00:58:27,480

696
00:58:41,210 --> 00:58:45,920
 The police have surrounded the house. If you go near the kitchen,

697
00:58:45,920 --> 00:58:48,910
 there's a door that leads to an alleyway.

698
00:58:48,910 --> 00:58:51,000
 Take that way out.

699
00:59:08,410 --> 00:59:11,230
Head to the second floor!

700
00:59:14,670 --> 00:59:16,920
Hey, check the veranda.

701
00:59:16,920 --> 00:59:19,610
Check inside there.

702
00:59:22,860 --> 00:59:24,850
Hey, over here!

